'A very good deed ye did, [placeholder]! We'll be off at once.'
Smala has asked you to bury supplies in the hope that they may return when the plains are safe from NÃºrzum's threat.
The fishermen's supplies can be gathered around their camp in the north-eastern Whitshaws.\n\nYou should gather the supplies.

The fishermen's home can be found south-west of their encampment on the lake.\n\nYou should bring the supplies to the homestead and bury them, in hopes that they will be useful in the future.
Smala can be found at the fishermen's encampment in the north-eastern Whitshaws.\n\nYou should tell Smala that you have buried his supplies where he wished.

'I'll pack up what I can, but most of this gear'll not travel well to Forlaw. I should hate to see it get into them hands of them Orcs.\n\n'Will ye bury some of our goods for us, friend? I'd like to think that we'll be back before long. Back at the house, if you would. We'll find 'em again.'
The Fishermen: Burying For Another Day
